total cash
and cash equivalents were $9.9 billion at the end of 2012, $3.1 billion lower
than the prior year. higher earnings and a higher adjustment for non-cash
transactions were more than offset by lower proceeds from sales of subsidiaries
and property, plant and equipment, a net debt decrease compared to a prior year
