investing activities
cash used in investment activities netted to $25.6
billion in 2012, $3.4 billion higher than 2011. spending for property, plant
and equipment of $34.3 billion increased $3.3 billion from 2011. proceeds
associated with sales of subsidiaries, property, plant and equipment, and sales
and returns of investments of $7.7 billion compared to $11.1 billion in 2011.
the decrease reflects that a $3.6 billion deposit was received in 2011 for a
sale that closed in 2012. additional investments and advances were $2.6 billion
lower in 2012.
cash used in investment activities netted to $22.2
billion in 2011, $2.0 billion lower than 2010. spending for property, plant and
equipment of $31.0 billion increased $4.1 billion from 2010. proceeds
associated with sales of subsidiaries, property, plant and equipment, and sales
and returns of investments of $11.1 billion compared to $3.3 billion in 2010.
the increase primarily reflects the sale of upstream canadian, u.k. and other
producing properties and assets, the sale of u.s. service stations, and a
$3.6billion deposit for a potential asset sale. additional investments
and advances were $2.3 billion higher in 2011.
